Prominent union leader Zwelinzima Vavi and his wife may lose their R3m mansion in Sandton that is wanted by creditors. Sunday World can reveal that 3GIP Proprietary Limited last month applied for a court judgment in the Johannesburg High Court to attach and auction off the Vavi's home in Morningside, north of Joburg. TO READ MORE ON THIS STORY GET A COPY OF TODAY'S SUNDAY WORLD